   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import arviz as az\n",
    "import bambi as bmb\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "from matplotlib.lines import Line2D"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.simplefilter(action='ignore', category=FutureWarning) # ArviZ\n",
    "\n",
    "az.style.use(\"arviz-doc\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rng = np.random.default_rng(121195)\n",
    "N = 200\n",
    "a, b = 0.5, 1.1\n",
    "x = rng.uniform(-1.5, 1.5, N)\n",
    "shape = np.exp(0.3 + x * 0.5 + rng.normal(scale=0.1, size=N))\n",
    "y = rng.gamma(shape, np.exp(a + b * x) / shape, N)\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame({\"x\": x, \"y\": y})\n",
    "new_data = pd.DataFrame({\"x\": np.linspace(-1.5, 1.5, num=50)})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "       Formula: y ~ x\n",
       "        Family: gamma\n",
       "          Link: mu = log\n",
       "  Observations: 200\n",
       "        Priors: \n",
       "    target = mu\n",
       "        Common-level effects\n",
       "            Intercept ~ Normal(mu: 0.0, sigma: 2.5037)\n",
       "            x ~ Normal(mu: 0.0, sigma: 2.8025)\n",
       "        \n",
       "        Auxiliary parameters\n",
       "            y_alpha ~ HalfCauchy(beta: 1.0)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "formula = bmb.Formula(\"y ~ x\")\n",
    "model = bmb.Model(formula, data, family=\"gamma\", link=\"log\")\n",
    "model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "idata = model.fit(random_seed=121195, idata_kwargs={\"log_likelihood\": True})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model.predict(idata, kind=\"mean\", data=new_data)\n",
    "model.predict(idata, kind=\"pps\", data=new_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "qts = (\n",
    "    az.extract(idata.posterior_predictive, var_names=\"y\")\n",
    "    .quantile([0.025, 0.975], \"sample\")\n",
    "    .to_numpy()\n",
    ")\n",
    "mean = az.extract(idata.posterior_predictive, var_names=\"y\").mean(\"sample\").to_numpy()"
   ]
  },

    "\n",
    "az.plot_hdi(new_data[\"x\"], qts, ax=ax, fill_kwargs={\"alpha\": 0.4})\n",

    "ax.scatter(data[\"x\"], data[\"y\"], alpha=0.8)\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel=\"Predictor\", ylabel=\"Outcome\");"

       "            alpha_Intercept ~ Normal(mu: 0.0, sigma: 1.0)\n",

  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The default link for the `mu` parameter is the **inverse** function. We want to use the **log** function instead. So let's set the link functions manually."
   ]
  },
  {

       "    target = alpha\n",
       "        Common-level effects\n",
       "            alpha_Intercept ~ Normal(mu: 0.0, sigma: 1.0)\n",

     "data": {

   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4.5), dpi=120)\n",
    "\n",
    "for idx in idata_d.posterior.coords.get(\"y_obs\"):\n",
    "    values = idata_d.posterior[\"y_alpha\"].sel(y_obs=idx).to_numpy().flatten()\n",
    "    grid, pdf = az.kde(values)\n",
    "    ax.plot(grid, pdf, lw=1, color=\"C0\", alpha=0.6)\n",
    "\n",
    "values = idata.posterior[\"y_alpha\"].to_numpy().flatten()\n",
    "grid, pdf = az.kde(values)\n",
    "ax.plot(grid, pdf, lw=1.5, color=\"black\");\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create legend\n",
    "handles = [\n",
    "    Line2D([0], [0], label=\"Varying alpha\", lw=1.5, color=\"C0\", alpha=0.6),\n",
    "    Line2D([0], [0], label=\"Constant alpha\", lw=1.5, color=\"black\")\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "legend = ax.legend(handles=handles, loc=\"upper right\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel=\"Alpha posterior\", ylabel=\"Density\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Gaussian response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = bmb.load_data(\"bikes\")\n",
    "data.sort_values(by=\"hour\", inplace=True)\n",
    "data_cnt_om = data[\"count\"].mean()\n",
    "data_cnt_os = data[\"count\"].std()\n",
    "data[\"count_normalized\"] = (data[\"count\"] - data_cnt_om) / data_cnt_os\n",
    "# Remove data, you may later try to refit the model to the whole data\n",
    "data = data[::50]\n",
    "data = data.reset_index(drop=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "\n",
    "mean = idata.posterior[\"count_normalized_mean\"].mean(dims).to_numpy()\n",
    "mean_interval = idata.posterior[\"count_normalized_mean\"].quantile(q, dims).to_numpy()\n",
    "y_interval = idata.posterior_predictive[\"count_normalized\"].quantile(q, dims).to_numpy()\n",

    "\n",
    "mean = idata.posterior[\"count_mean\"].mean(dims).to_numpy()\n",
    "mean_interval = idata.posterior[\"count_mean\"].quantile(q, dims).to_numpy()\n",
    "y_interval = idata.posterior_predictive[\"count\"].quantile(q, dims).to_numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4.5), dpi=120)\n",
    "ax.scatter(data[\"hour\"], data[\"count\"], alpha=0.3, color=\"C0\", zorder=5)\n",
    "ax.plot(hour, mean, color=\"C3\", zorder=5)\n",
    "ax.fill_between(hour, mean_interval[0],mean_interval[1], alpha=0.5, color=\"C1\");\n",

    "data2 = data.loc[(data[\"hour\"] < 10) | (data[\"hour\"] > 15)]\n",
    "formula = bmb.Formula(\n",
    "    \"count ~ 0 + bs(hour, 8, intercept=True)\",\n",
    "    \"alpha ~ 0 + bs(hour, 8, intercept=True)\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "model = bmb.Model(formula, data, family=\"gamma\", link={\"mu\": \"log\", \"alpha\": \"log\"})\n",
    "idata = model.fit()\n",
    "model.predict(idata, data=new_data, kind=\"pps\")"
